M. GRACE MURPHY, ADMINISTRATRIX OF THE ESTATE OF JOHN H. MURPHY, DECEASED, v. THE UNITED STATES [No. D-921. Decided June 3, 1929] *150Mr. Hugh W. Ogden for the plaintiff. Messrs. Edward O. Proctor and Q. I. Abrams were on the briefs. Messrs. Dwight E. Rorer and Dan M. Jackson, with whom was Mr. Assistant Attorney General Herman J. Galloway, for the defendant. Madam Loyola M. Goyne was on the brief. *168Sinnott, Judge; and GReen, Judge, concur.

Gsai-iam, Judge, took no part in the decision of this case; and Moss, Judge, took no part on account of illness.
